HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 292
By Bricken
A RESOLUTION to honor Kelly Orr on her selection as the 2025
Tennessee Arts Academy Teacher Hero.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly specially recognize
those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the highest-quality
education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Kelly Orr is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished herself as
a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Orr, a fine arts teacher at Tullahoma High School, was recently named
a 2025 Tennessee Arts Academy Teacher Hero, an honor most befitting her unwavering
dedication to her students; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Arts Academy is the nation's premier summer professional
development institute for arts education; held annually since 1986 on the campus of Middle
Tennessee State University, the academy provides cutting-edge training for more than 325 K-12
arts educators; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Arts Academy Teacher Hero award is a peer-nominated
award presented to a teacher who exemplifies the highest standard of excellence in teaching,
engaging students through talent and creativity to go above and beyond in helping them
succeed in the classroom, the arts, and life; and
WHEREAS, Kelly Orr is an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike, and her
friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Orr truly epitomizes the dedicated arts teacher who is wholly committed
to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
